The Chronicle Walter Mswazie, Masvingo Correspondent SANDRA Ndebele, gospel singer Blessing Shumba and Afro Pop artiste Andy Muridzo, will be performing at a musical concert in Masvingo that will be held in memory of those who perished in the Cyclone Idai disaster. The family show on Saturday has been organised by promotions company King Lee Promotions in partnership with Simuka Upenye Integrated Youth Academy (SIYA) and will take place at Mucheke Stadium. Two hundred and fifty lives have been lost with thousands being displaced and over 500 missing in Chimanimani, Chipinge, Bikita, Zaka, Gutu and Masvingo as a result of the cyclone. <img class="size-medium wp-image-442580" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Blessing-Shumba-1-360x280.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="280" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Blessing-Shumba-1-360x280.jpg 360w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Blessing-Shumba-1-768x597.jpg 768w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Blessing-Shumba-1-680x529.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2019/03/Blessing-Shumba-1.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px" /> Blessing Shumba Kinglee Promotions spokesperson Liberty Chaira said they were touched by the plight of the Cylcone Idai victims hence why they decided to mobilise people to donate through this musical concert. Entrance into the venue will be a donation (foodstuff, money or clothes/blankets). “The extent of the damage by Cyclone Idai motivated us to give a helping hand. We approached the artistes who agreed to perform for free and we hope to receive a lot of goods that will be used by those affected by the cyclone,” said Chaira. – @walterbmswazie2